-- China's Power Restrictions Affect Aluminum More Than Steel, Macquarie Says
-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 2010-10-16T08:35:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-16/china-s-power-restrictions-affect-aluminum-more-than-steel-macquarie-says.html
China’s power restrictions “has
been greater and is likely to be more long-lasting on aluminium
than on steel,” Macquarie Group Ltd. said in a report.  Macquarie has a “positive view” on aluminum prices for
the fourth quarter, according to the report dated Oct. 18.
“However, any near-term strength in aluminium prices would
encourage the quick ramp-up of new projects next year, once the
pressure from Beijing eases.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  